#
# checkstyle is the **de-facto Java code-style verifier**
# — checks Java source against a configurable style
# guide (e.g. Google Java Style, Sun Code Conventions).
# Used in CI pipelines for thousands of Java projects.
# Pivots from Rust lexopt (R275 jiff-cli) into the
# **Java language tooling cluster**.  Sister to Java
# tooling (javac / javap / jshell / spotbugs / pmd).
# **MAJOR MILESTONE**: corpus's **first documented Java
# picocli CLI** — adds Java to the cross-language CLI
# taxonomy (15 library variants now).
#
# Critical extraction note: checkstyle uses **picocli**
# library — corpus's **first documented Java picocli
# CLI** AND first use of the **picocli ecosystem**.
# picocli is **the** standard modern Java CLI library
# — used by Quarkus, GraalVM native-image, Helidon,
# Micronaut, Spring Boot's CLI, and most other
# enterprise Java tools.  Extends the **cross-language
# CLI taxonomy** to FIFTEEN library variants: Rust
# (clap derive/builder/v3/hand-rolled/pico_args/lexopt
# — 6); Go (cobra/pflag/flaggy/stdlib flag — 4);
# Python (Click/argparse/Typer — 3); Crystal
# OptionParser; Haskell optparse-applicative; OCaml
# Cmdliner; C POSIX getopt; **Java picocli** (R276 —
# NEW).  Documents the **picocli pattern**:
# annotation-driven CLI definition similar to Spring
# Boot's annotation-based configuration:
#   `@Command(name = "...", description = "...",
#            mixinStandardHelpOptions = true)`
#       — class annotation marking the CLI class
#   `@Option(names = {"-x", "--long"}, description = "...")`
#       — field annotation marking a flag
#   `@Parameters(arity = "1..*", paramLabel = "...",
#                description = "...")`
#       — field annotation marking positional args
# Distinct from Rust clap derive's struct-attribute
# approach (R247 sncast etc.) — picocli uses Java
# annotations which are RUNTIME-REFLECTED (slower than
# clap's compile-time macros but allows dynamic
# inspection).
#
# Critical extraction note: checkstyle uses
# **`mixinStandardHelpOptions = true`** at Main.java:642
# — picocli's **standard help-and-version mixin** that
# AUTO-ADDS `-h/--help` and `-V/--version` flags to
# the command.  Documents the **mixin pattern in
# picocli** — a reusable bundle of flags/options that
# can be added to any `@Command`.  Distinct from clap
# derive's manual `version = ...` + auto-`-h/--help`
# (R247+) and from Click's manual `--version` decorator
# (R266 uvicorn).  picocli ships several stock mixins
# (StandardHelpOptions, HelpCommand, etc.).  Corpus's
# **first documented picocli mixin** pattern.
#
# Critical extraction note: checkstyle uses **picocli
# template interpolation in description strings** —
# `${DEFAULT-VALUE}` at Main.java:717 (rendered as the
# field's default value at help-text generation time)
# and `${COMPLETION-CANDIDATES}` at Main.java:745
# (rendered as the enum's values at help-text generation
# time).  E.g. `description = "... Defaults to
# ${DEFAULT-VALUE}."` becomes `... Defaults to 1.` for
# `tabWidth = 8`.  And `description = "... Valid values:
# ${COMPLETION-CANDIDATES} ..."` becomes `... Valid
# values: XML, SARIF, PLAIN ...` for the OutputFormat
# enum.  Documents the **picocli template-string
# interpolation** pattern — distinct from clap derive's
# manual `default_value_t = ...` + auto-include in
# help (R260 dua) and from Click's `show_default=True`
# (R266 uvicorn).  picocli's approach lets the
# developer EXPLICITLY POSITION the default/enum
# values within the description text.  Corpus's
# **first documented picocli template interpolation**.
#
# Critical extraction note: checkstyle uses **enum-as-
# Option-type** at Main.java:564-570 + 743-747 — the
# `OutputFormat` enum (XML / SARIF / PLAIN) is used
# as the field type of the `-f` option.  picocli
# auto-detects enum types and (a) restricts CLI values
# to the enum constants, (b) auto-renders the values
# via `${COMPLETION-CANDIDATES}`.  Documents the
# **enum-as-Option-type pattern** in picocli —
# equivalent to clap's `#[derive(ValueEnum)]` (R247+)
# and Click's `click.Choice([...])` (R266 uvicorn).
# But picocli's approach is more minimal: just use a
# regular Java enum; picocli's reflection does the
# rest.
#
# Critical extraction note: checkstyle uses **dual-
# purpose AST-printing flags** with mutual exclusion
# documented in help text — at Main.java:750-777 the
# `-t/--tree`, `-T/--treeWithComments`, `-j/--javadocTree`,
# `-J/--treeWithJavadoc` all share the constraint
# "can only be used on a single file and cannot be
# combined with other options" but the constraint is
# enforced AT RUNTIME (in validate()), not via
# picocli's declarative attributes.  Documents the
# **runtime mutex validation** pattern in picocli —
# distinct from R258 bevy's clap `conflicts_with_all
# = [...]` (declarative) and R250 sozo's `#[group(
# multiple = false)]` (declarative).  picocli has
# `@ArgGroup(exclusive = true)` for declarative
# mutex but checkstyle chose runtime enforcement for
# more flexible error messages.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line

# OutputFormat enum at Main.java:564-570.
local -a output_formats=(
  'XML:XMLLogger output (xml/xpath-friendly)'
  'SARIF:SARIF logger output (Static Analysis Results Interchange Format; CI integration)'
  'PLAIN:DefaultLogger output (default; plain text to stdout)'
)

# 17 @Option fields + 1 @Parameters positional decoded
# source-direct from CliOptions at Main.java:643-817.
_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help (picocli mixinStandardHelpOptions)]' \
  '(-V --version)'{-V,--version}'[show version (picocli mixinStandardHelpOptions)]' \
  '-c+[location of the configuration XML file (filesystem path OR ClassLoader resource name)]:file:_files -g "*.xml"' \
  '-o+[output file (default: stdout)]:file:_files' \
  '-p+[properties file to load]:file:_files -g "*.properties"' \
  '-s+[print xpath suppressions at line:col (e.g. -s 25:7)]:line\:col:' \
  '(-w --tabWidth)'{-w+,--tabWidth=}'[tab character length (default: 8; used with -s)]:n:' \
  '(-g --generate-xpath-suppression)'{-g,--generate-xpath-suppression}'[generate output xpath suppression XML to suppress all violations]' \
  '(-G --generate-checks-and-files-suppression)'{-G,--generate-checks-and-files-suppression}'[generate output checks-and-files suppression XML]' \
  '-f+[output format (picocli ${COMPLETION-CANDIDATES} renders these from OutputFormat enum)]:format:(($output_formats))' \
  '(-t --tree)'{-t,--tree}'[print AST (no comments) of a single file; cannot combine with other options]' \
  '(-T --treeWithComments)'{-T,--treeWithComments}'[print AST with comments (no javadoc); cannot combine with other options]' \
  '(-j --javadocTree)'{-j,--javadocTree}'[print parse tree of a javadoc comment; cannot combine with other options]' \
  '(-J --treeWithJavadoc)'{-J,--treeWithJavadoc}'[print AST with javadoc nodes; cannot combine with other options]' \
  '(-d --debug)'{-d,--debug}'[print all debug logging]' \
  '*'{-e+,--exclude=}'[directory/file to exclude (repeatable; List<File> field)]:path:_files' \
  '*'{-x+,--exclude-regexp=}'[directory/file pattern to exclude (regex; repeatable; List<Pattern> field)]:regex:' \
  '(-E --executeIgnoredModules)'{-E,--executeIgnoredModules}'[allow ignored modules to be run]' \
  '(-b --branch-matching-xpath)'{-b+,--branch-matching-xpath=}'[show AST branches matching given XPath query]:xpath:' \
  '*:source files or folders to verify (@Parameters arity = "1..*"):_files'
